&lt;div class="article-hero-img" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1a2a1a,#0a1a0a);height:200px;border-radius:8px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:1.5rem;"&gt;
&lt;span style="font-family:Orbitron,sans-serif;font-size:1.8rem;font-weight:900;color:#6abe30;"&gt;MAIN BUS LAYOUT&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-is-a-main-bus"&gt;What Is a Main Bus?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;main bus&lt;/strong&gt; is a set of parallel belts (the &amp;quot;bus&amp;quot;) carrying raw materials through your base. Assembly blocks &lt;strong&gt;pull&lt;/strong&gt; from the bus and &lt;strong&gt;push&lt;/strong&gt; finished products back onto it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think of it like a highway: resources flow down the middle, factories are off-ramps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="recommended-bus-width"&gt;Recommended Bus Width&lt;/h2&gt;
